  "status": "draft",
  "description": "Adults aged 50 to 80 years (inclusive both ways, i.e., >=50, <= 80) who have a 30 pack-year smoking history and currently smoke or have quit within the past 15 years. Screening should be discontinued once a person has not smoked for 15 years (identical to inclusion criterion above) or develops a health problem that substantially limits life expectancy or the ability or willingness to have curative lung surgery (currently NOT taken into account.)",
  "purpose": "Annual screening for lung cancer with low-dose computed tomography (LDCT)",
